= Feature: Guest Mode

image:guest.png[float="right", width="240"]

A *patient* can use the Symptom Check without registering in "Guest Mode" so that users who have no QID can also use the app.

== Rule: Guest Mode is available at the login screen

== Example: Guest Mode Button

- Given an anonymous user
- When they click on the "Guest Mode" button
- Then they are redirected to the Inteview
- But they need to manually add demographics data
+
Example: Age, sex, location

A user can choose to run a Symptoms Check interview for another person so that they can help a friend or a family member who does not have the app installed.

image:interview_another.png[]

== Rule: Only available for logged-in users

= Feature: Interview

= Feature: Log-in

image:patient.png[float="right", width="240"]

A *patient* can log-in to the platform to keep track of their symptom check history, manage their profile, share results etc.

== Rule: Authentication is available only for Qatari citizens

Inputting a QID that is registered in NAS will automatically log the user in.

=== Example: Login with Qatar ID (QID)

image:login.png[]

== Rule: First login creates user

When a user authenticates for the first time their account is created in the Symptom Checker's system.

Their personal information is dispalyed for verification.

== Rule: Personal information is loaded from NAS

When logging in available personal information is loaded from NAS and saved to the Symptom Checker's system.

Example:

- First Name / Last Name
- Age, Sex, Location, Address

== Rule: Patient can navigate to NAS to Register Their QID

If the patient's QID is not registered with NAS they can go to it and register.

= Feature: Profile Management

A user can manage their profile and update some information like contact details so that they can receive notifications on another phone.

== Rule: Secondary email and phone number are the only editable fields

**NAS** stands for **N**ational **A**uthentication **S**ervice

Original personal information from NAS cannot be modified

image:profile.png[]

=== Scenario Template: Editable Fields

- Given A "<field>"
- When B
- Then C "<is editable>"

==== Examples:

[cols="2,1"]
|===
| field     | is editable

|    email  | ☑
|    phone  | ☑
|    name   | ☒
|===
